=================================================================
CREATE DATAFRAME - INTERVIEW SUMMARY (30 Sec Answers)
=================================================================

Q1: How to create DataFrame in Spark?
A: 4 ways - from list/tuple, from CSV/JSON/Parquet, from RDD, from JDBC

Q2: Syntax?
A: spark.createDataFrame(data=data, schema=schema)

Q3: What if no schema provided?
A: Spark infers automatically but slower. ALWAYS provide schema for production.

Q4: How to handle pipe-delimited data from Notepad?
A: df = spark.read.option("delimiter", "|").csv("file.txt")

Q5: createDataFrame() vs toDF()?
A: createDataFrame from SparkSession, toDF converts RDD to DataFrame

=================================================================
REAL-TIME INTERVIEW QUESTIONS
=================================================================

Q: You get 10GB pipe-delimited file from legacy system. How do you create DataFrame?

A: 
df = spark.read \
    .option("delimiter", "|") \
    .option("header", "true") \
    .schema(custom_schema) \
    .csv("s3://path/file.txt")
# Why? Pipe common in mainframe data. Always provide schema for 10GB file.

Q: Daily CSV arrives with 200 columns but you need only 5. What's your approach?

A: 
schema = StructType([StructField("id", IntegerType()), StructField("name", StringType())])
df = spark.read.schema(schema).csv("file.csv")
# Spark reads only those 5 columns - faster, less memory

Q: Your DataFrame creation is slow. Why?

A: Top reasons:
1. inferSchema=true → Disable, provide explicit schema
2. No header → Use header=true or provide schema  
3. Small files → Use coalesce() before creating DF

Q: How to create empty DataFrame with 100 columns for testing?

A: 
schema = StructType([StructField(f"col_{i}", StringType()) for i in range(100)])
empty_df = spark.createDataFrame([], schema)

Q: Client sends data in Notepad with mixed delimiter (| and ,). How to handle?

A: 
# Clean in Python first
lines = open("file.txt").read().replace("|", ",").split("\n")
data = [tuple(line.split(",")) for line in lines if line]
df = spark.createDataFrame(data, schema)

