union vs unionAll | Lec-13 | spark interview questions



=================================================================
UNION vs UNION ALL - INTERVIEW CRAM
=================================================================

Q1: Difference between union() and unionAll()?
A: In Spark - BOTH do same thing (UNION ALL - no duplicate removal)
   - union() = unionAll() = keeps all rows including duplicates
   - Traditional SQL: UNION removes dupes, UNION ALL keeps dupes
   - Spark: unionByName() available for column matching

Q2: What happens to number of rows?
A: union() - adds rows. No removal.
   df1.count() = 100, df2.count() = 50 → union = 150 rows

Q3: What if columns are in different order?
A: union() - column POSITION matters, names don't matter
   unionByName() - column NAMES matter, position doesn't matter

Q4: What if column names are different?
A: union() - works if data types match (ignores names)
   unionByName() - fails, needs same column names

Q5: What is unionByName()?
A: Matches by column name instead of position.
   Reorders columns automatically to align names
